text: Les Reed (born 16 August 1932) is a former Australian rules footballer. He played for Geelong in the Victorian Football League (VFL) during the early 1950s. He came off the bench as a reserve in Geelong's 1951 premiership side. He also played as a wingman when they lost the 1953 Grand Final to Collingwood. ==References== ==Other websites== * Les Reed stats at AFL Tables Category:1932 births Category:Living people Category:Australian rules footballers Category:Sportspeople from Victoria (Australia)
